const categoryTranslations = {"bodyDiameter":"Body Diameter","bonds":"Bond","eyeColor":"Eye Color","eyeSize":"Eye Size","eyestalkShape":"Eyestalk Size","eyestalkTexture":"Eyestalk Texture","flaws":"Flaw","greaterMinions":"Greater Minions","ideals":"Ideal","irisShape":"Iris Shape","lesserMinions":"Lesser Minions","mouthSizeAndShape":"Mouth Size and Shape","names":"Name","personalityTraits":"Personality Trait","pets":"Pets","skinColor":"Skin Color","skinTexture":"Skin Texture","teethShape":"Teeth Shape","unusualFeatures":"Unusual Feature","honorifics":"Honorific","personalityTrait":"Personality Trait","physicalFeatures":"Physical Feature","demonicInfluence":"Demonic Influence","leader":"Leader","sharedPhysicalTrait":"Shared Physical Trait","specialCreatures":"Special Creatures","tactics":"Tactic","brutes":"Brutes","objects":"Object","servants":"Servants","scaleColor":"Scale Color","trophies":"Trophies"}
let reproduction = ["<b>Spontaneous Reincarnation.</b> When an adult or older dragon dies, one or more eggs form in the dragon\u2019s decomposing body. These eggs might grow like fungus as the body rots away, they could appear among the ashes after the body is consumed by fire, or they might need to be mined out from a corpse that has turned to solid stone or metal.", "<b>Seedlings of the First World.</b> At the heart of the world (underground, or in a remote area of pristine wilderness) stands a tree on which dragon eggs grow like fruit. Once in a lifetime, each dragon feels an overwhelming urge to seek out this tree. After finding it, the dragon must persuade its guardian to relinquish one or more eggs.", "<b>Consuming Treasure.</b> By eating a significant portion of their own hoards, dragons cause themselves to lay clutches of eggs.", "<b>Magical Crafting.</b> Mirroring the creative acts of Bahamut and Tiamat, dragons craft their eggs through painstaking labor, then breathe the gift of life into them.", "<b>Draconic Transformation.</b> Enlightened non-dragons (most often Humanoids) are transformed into dragon eggs when they die, when they experience profound enlightenment, or when they undergo a ritual that might involve bathing in dragon blood or being devoured by a dragon. Humanoids and dragons alike understand the transformation to be a transition into a higher state of existence.", "<b>Divine Origin.</b> Only Bahamut and Tiamat can create dragon eggs\u2014each egg is the result of divine intervention.", "<b>Spontaneous Formation.</b> Dragon eggs arise naturally in certain regions, often in underground veins of metal ore or gems for metallic and gem dragons, respectively, or in extreme environments (volcanoes, arctic wastes, deadly swamps, and so forth) for chromatic dragons. The eggs might hatch on their own, or they might have to be unearthed first by another creature, whether that\u2019s an adult or older dragon or a hapless miner.", "<b>Parthenogenesis.</b> An adult or older dragon can lay a clutch of eggs whenever the dragon feels ready to rear a clutch of wyrmlings\u2014or to impose that responsibility on others.", "<b>Dragon Conclave.</b> Five adult or older dragons of different kinds come together to create a clutch of eggs, with each giving up a bit of life energy as part of the process. This clutch of eggs hatches five dragons of different kinds, depending on the dragons making up the conclave.", "<b>Rejuvenation.</b> An ancient dragon voluntarily enters a deep trance and eventually dies, leaving behind a single egg."]
let goalsAncient = ["Avoid decline by becoming Undead or seeking magical alternatives to aging", "Transcend the limits of physical existence on a single world by uniting echoes across multiple worlds or establishing a lair on another plane of existence", "Acquire a particular artifact, perhaps to complete a set (all three parts of the Regalia of Evil, the Eye of Vecna and Hand of Vecna, and so forth)", "Collect a complete set of artistic treasures, such as all the paintings of a great master, manuscripts for a famed author\u2019s entire body of writings, or every piece of jewelry made by a master artisan", "Transform an entire world into an extreme environment suitable as a lair\u2014a volcanic hellscape, a frozen wonderland, an arid wasteland, or the like", "Destroy one or more gods as an act of vengeance or to ascend to godhood"]
let flaws = ["I find adventurers fearsome, and I\u2019m convinced that I\u2019ll meet my doom at their hands one day.", "One item in my possession is worth as much as the rest of my hoard combined, and the fear that it might be stolen consumes me.", "Given the opportunity, I eat to excess and then fall into a long, deep sleep.", "I would rather let my fearsome reputation scare away intruders than fight them off.", "Other dragons would scorn me if they knew how fondly I regard my minions. They\u2019re so cute!", "I am terrified of creatures from the Outer Planes\u2014especially modrons.", "Another dragon has sworn to find and destroy me.", "Humanoids are not ready to learn the horrible cosmic truths in the books in my hoard.", "The prospect of living for centuries more exhausts me.", "I\u2019m convinced that a version of me on a different world in the Material Plane is hoping to destroy me and steal my hoard."]
let goalsYoung = ["Establish a lair and develop the land around it to maximize safety and good hunting", "Amass as much treasure as possible", "Acquire magical wards to help protect the lair", "Sabotage the efforts of other young dragons to establish lairs in the local area", "Earn the fear and respect of other creatures living near the lair through displays of power", "Secure the allegiance of loyal and powerful minions"]
let mannerisms = ["Rotates head from side to side when listening or speaking", "Tail writhes constantly in a snakelike fashion", "Slowly and constantly fans wings", "Lowers head to speak eye-to-eye to smaller creatures\u2014unless angry", "Uses Draconic words and phrases even when speaking other languages", "Punctuates speech with bestial sounds\u2014growls, roars, croaks, chirps, or whistles", "Fiddles with tip of tail", "Absently chews on or picks at teeth with swords, spears, or lances", "Quickly forgets names and invents random nicknames instead", "Burdens conversation with extensive historical context, whether or not it\u2019s relevant", "Constantly twitches tail\u2014and occasionally pounces on it", "Speaks an archaic form of Common (equivalent to Shakespearean English) and doesn\u2019t understand contemporary slang and idioms", "Prone to uttering terrifying, guttural sounds, which are actually laughter", "Enjoys mimicking Humanoid voices", "Dismisses modern cultures as historical curiosities sure to collapse imminently", "Has trouble discerning details of anything as small as Humanoids", "Sharpens claws or horns on nearby stone surfaces", "Manifests small signs of the breath weapon, such as exhaling smoke rings, setting arc lightning dancing over teeth, or blowing acid bubbles", "Sighs restlessly, giving an impression of tremendous boredom", "Deeply suspicious, treating all Humanoids encountered as probable agents of a rival dragon"]
let echoCharacteristics = ["Same dragon kind and age, differing only in physical appearance", "Same dragon kind and age, differing only in a peculiar mannerism", "Same dragon kind and age, but significantly different in personality, ideals, or alignment", "Same dragon kind and generally alike, but older or younger by one category", "Same age, different kind within the same family (chromatic, gem, or metallic), and similar in appearance and personality", "Same age, different kind in a different family (with a similar breath weapon or habitat), with similar appearance but very different ideals or alignment", "Radically different in almost every way imaginable but still bound by fate across the worlds", "Roll again, and in addition the echo is Undead (a dracolich, hollow dragon, ghost dragon, or draconic shard) or a shadow dragon."]
let undeadAdventureHooks = ["A dragon seeks help, desperate to prevent a dracolich-worshiping cult from convincing the dragon\u2019s sibling, mate, or rival to become a dracolich.", "A dragon suffering from a wasting affliction asks the characters to travel to another world, where they must destroy an echo of that dragon who has become a dracolich.", "A pirate crew under the command of a ghost dragon fights to recover the dead dragon\u2019s scattered hoard.", "A hollow dragon guards an artifact meant to be used in the dire circumstances foretold in an ancient prophecy. Now the prophecy is coming to pass, but the dragon won\u2019t let the artifact be used for its intended purpose.", "A gem dragon from another world is searching for the dragon\u2019s echo, which has become a draconic shard.", "A dracolich keeps returning after being destroyed. The dracolich\u2019s connection to its echoes on other worlds is keeping its soul intact, like a phylactery, and the connection must be severed before the creature\u2019s threat can be ended."]
let encounterComplications = ["The dragon has no interest in fighting and tries to avoid the characters, until they anger the dragon through significantly injury or insult.", "The dragon is too bored to fight and offers the characters a tiny amount of treasure if they\u2019ll leave.", "The dragon hates a certain type of character (sneaky rogues, healers, or heavily armored fighters, perhaps) and directs at least one attack each round at such a character.", "The dragon tries to drive the characters off by emotionally hurting or humiliating them\u2014threatening something they obviously care about, damaging their equipment, insulting them, or showing how ineffectual their attacks are.", "The dragon has a way to call for help hidden deep inside the lair, such as a magic horn that summons minions, an iron flask with a powerful Fiend inside, or a magic portal to an echo\u2019s lair. The characters must prevent the dragon from summoning aid or face a new threat.", "The dragon is desperately trying to protect a particular treasure, one or more eggs, or perhaps a minion, bargaining to protect this treasure and flying into a rage if it is harmed.", "The previous occupant of the dragon\u2019s lair left behind a curse, a trap, or a lingering spirit that clever characters can turn against the dragon.", "The dragon\u2019s lair is almost impossible to navigate without access to one or more of the dragon\u2019s special movement modes (typically flight, but possibly burrowing, swimming, or climbing).", "It\u2019s been so long since anyone has dared to intrude on the dragon\u2019s lair that the dragon is more interested in showing off the lair\u2014and impressive lair actions\u2014than in doing serious harm to the characters. If the characters escape and spread stories of the dragon\u2019s grandeur, so much the better.", "When the dragon is agitated, the regional effects that alter the terrain around the lair create visible changes around the dragon each round.", "Factions and grudges within the ranks of the dragon\u2019s minions erupt when the characters challenge the dragon, resulting in infighting that might tip the odds in the main battle in either direction.", "A feature in the dragon\u2019s lair has an unpredictable magical effect, perhaps similar to a wand of wonder, a sorcerer\u2019s wild magic surge, or a dungeon trick as described in the Dungeon Master\u2019s Guide. The dragon avoids the feature unless the encounter is going badly, then either activates the feature or tries to goad the characters into doing so.", "Spell effects and breath weapons used inside the dragon\u2019s lair cause dramatic destruction, including chasms opening up, ceilings collapsing, pillars toppling, and other effects that can damage or hinder the characters and the dragon equally.", "The dragon has a rival who notices the characters approaching the dragon\u2019s lair and keeps tabs on the fight. This rival might step in to help the characters or the dragon, depending on the circumstances, or might ambush the characters when they leave the dragon\u2019s lair.", "The dragon takes tremendous pleasure in adopting Humanoid form and pretending to be a minion, groveling and sniveling when intruders enter the lair and claiming that the dragon is away.", "The dragon\u2019s only goal is to learn a key piece of information about the characters\u2019 larger goals and then escape.", "The dragon enjoys combat, roaring in appreciation each time the characters pull off effective attacks or flashy spells. But if seriously hurt, the dragon quickly calls for a truce.", "Each round of combat with the dragon, the characters catch an eerie glimpse of another world where one of the dragon\u2019s echoes is active.", "The dragon has a plan to feign death in case of attack\u2014apparently being buried in a cave-in, tumbling into a deep chasm, drowning in lava, or some similarly dramatic exit. After escaping, the dragon plots revenge.", "At the same time the characters are confronting the dragon, another group of adventurers is confronting one of the dragon\u2019s echoes on another world. Halfway through the fight, either the dragons or the characters and the other adventurers switch places."]
let halfDragonOrigin = ["<b>Regional Effects.</b> The magical influence of a dragon\u2019s lair causes half-dragons to spontaneously arise among the area\u2019s other creatures.", "<b>Forbidden Fruit.</b> A dragon can cause a particular tree to produce magical fruit. When eaten by a creature able to bear children, the fruit causes the creature to bear a half-dragon.", "<b>True Love\u2019s Gift.</b> Love occasionally blossoms between dragons and creatures of other kinds, and this life bond can result in half-dragon children. Most half-dragons born of love are created as a magical gift.", "<b>Blood Transformation.</b> A creature that bathes in or drinks the blood of a dragon can sometimes be transformed into a half-dragon. A dragon might voluntarily offer some blood to bring this about, or it could happen accidentally when a would-be dragonslayer is splashed with dragon blood.", "<b>Cradle Favor.</b> A dragon might bestow the gift of draconic power on a newborn baby or an unborn child\u2014as either a blessing or a curse.", "<b>Hoard Thieves.</b> The hoard of an older dragon is imbued with that dragon\u2019s power. Those who steal from such a hoard might transform into halfdragons as that power leaches into them."]
let lairLocation = ["The area is a climate anomaly\u2014a cool and lush oasis in a hot desert, a balmy spring within a frozen tundra, a drifting iceberg in a warm sea, a barren waste in the midst of a verdant forest, or the like.", "The area is a wild magic zone. Whenever a creature casts a spell of 1st level or higher or activates a magic item, roll a d10. On a 1, roll on the Wild Magic Surge table in the Player\u2019s Handbook.", "Natural rock formations align with celestial phenomena at particular times of the year. Stars and planets might line up with rock spires and windows on solstices and equinoxes, for example.", "A dead god or titan is buried in the area.", "The area is a vast crater, at the center of which is a long-buried meteorite.", "A magical portal to another plane of existence releases dangerous energy\u2014and sometimes creatures\u2014into the area.", "The area was a battlefield in an ancient war where thousands of soldiers were annihilated in a devastating magical assault.", "Gravity does not function as expected in the area, which might manifest as giant floating earth motes or similar terrain.", "An enormous tree\u2014possibly the oldest living organism in the world\u2014grows at the heart of the area.", "A god left a profound impression on the site during an ancient visit to the Material Plane\u2014perhaps a footprint, a pool of tears, or a splash of blood that has permanently infused the ground."]
let appearance = ["Draconic letters or symbols engraved on prominent scales", "Large scar", "One eye missing or milky", "Crooked teeth", "Notably overweight or underweight", "Elongated, sinuous body", "Shortened, stocky body", "Coins or gems embedded in hide", "Sculpted horns or claws", "Rings piercing crest or wing edges", "Draped in some semblance of clothing, from a stole to a full robe", "Unusual coloration (for example, a red dragon with an orange, brown, or purple cast)", "Crouched, predatory posture like a stalking cat\u2019s", "Erect, almost bipedal posture", "Scales covered with painted handprints of minions, admirers, or children", "Necklaces made of bones, horns, claws, or teeth taken from enemies", "Extra horns or spines", "Elongated, fang-like teeth, or extra rows of teeth", "Sharpened or serrated scales", "Elemental energy matching the dragon\u2019s breath weapon, seeping out between the scales"]
let bonds = ["I treasure one particular item in my hoard\u2014a gift from a person I loved, who is long since dead.", "I am close to my siblings, whose lairs are nearby. I would go to great lengths to protect them\u2014or avenge them.", "A nearby person intrigues me with fascinating questions and bizarre ideas.", "I collect information about the worlds of the Material Plane, and I would love to visit another world someday.", "I am devoted to Bahamut or Tiamat and put their interests ahead of my own.", "I\u2019m determined to destroy the adventurers who slew my parent\u2014and everyone connected to them.", "I\u2019m obsessed with attracting the attention of another dragon.", "I feel an obligation to protect the creatures that inhabit my territory (except the ones I eat).", "I am trying to collect an extremely rare set of priceless treasures.", "I won\u2019t rest until I retrieve an item stolen from my hoard."]
let goalsAdult = ["Find a good location for an additional lair", "Acquire an artifact or a powerful magic item for the hoard", "Establish a dynastic bloodline by producing young", "Eliminate younger dragons who could become rivals or threats if they are allowed to grow older", "Transform a large region into an environment suitable for the dragon\u2019s preferred sort of lair", "Develop dragonsight to pursue goals across multiple worlds"]
let goalsWyrmling = ["Establish independence from adult dragons (or other powerful creatures)", "Acquire one valuable magic item or art object to build a hoard around", "Acquire minions who will bring food and treasure", "Establish dominance over other wyrmlings in the same brood", "Secure a partnership with a more powerful creature for safety", "Find a good spot for a first independent lair"]
